Sentencas: Intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs), as the operating temperature decreases, require cathode materials with high catalytic activity.
Titulo: Double Perovskite Sr2CoFeO5+δ: Preparation and Performance as Cathode Material for Intermediate-temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this study, double perovskite Sr2CoFeO5+delta (SCF) was synthesized by Sol-Gel method, and effect of SCF cathode compounded with 20% (molar fraction) Sm2O3 doped CeO2 (SDC) at different ratios on the electrode performance was elucidated.
Titulo: Double Perovskite Sr2CoFeO5+δ: Preparation and Performance as Cathode Material for Intermediate-temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The SOFC single-cell performance was improved by optimized chemical expansion and area-specific resistance (ASR) from composite electrodes.
Titulo: Double Perovskite Sr2CoFeO5+δ: Preparation and Performance as Cathode Material for Intermediate-temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Results show that, SCF cathode after annealing at 950 degrees C for 10 h exhibits good chemical compatibility with common electrolytes.
Titulo: Double Perovskite Sr2CoFeO5+δ: Preparation and Performance as Cathode Material for Intermediate-temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: For the composite of SCF and SDC at a mass ratio of 1 : 1, the average thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) can be significantly reduced from 2.44x10(-5) K-1 of pure SCF to 1.54x10(-5) K-1.
Titulo: Double Perovskite Sr2CoFeO5+δ: Preparation and Performance as Cathode Material for Intermediate-temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: ASR of SCF-xSDC (x=20, 30, 40, 50, x: mass percentage) composite cathodes are as low as 0.036, 0.034, 0.028 and 0.092 Omega center dot cm(2) at 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Double Perovskite Sr2CoFeO5+δ: Preparation and Performance as Cathode Material for Intermediate-temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The SCF-40SDC composite cathode displays the lowest ASR value among SCF-xSDC in the whole temperature range.
Titulo: Double Perovskite Sr2CoFeO5+δ: Preparation and Performance as Cathode Material for Intermediate-temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Based on the 0.3 mm-thick La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) electrolyte, the maximum power density of SOFC using SCF-40SDC (757 mW center dot cm(-2)) as a cathode is higher than that of pure SCF (684 mW center dot cm(-2)).
Titulo: Double Perovskite Sr2CoFeO5+δ: Preparation and Performance as Cathode Material for Intermediate-temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: These results demonstrate that the SCF-40SDC composite cathode is a promising candidate for application in IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Double Perovskite Sr2CoFeO5+δ: Preparation and Performance as Cathode Material for Intermediate-temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
